Also called anaerobic zone. In this you\'ll get the greatest health benefits overall. Your heart and lung capacity will increase and your overall fitness will also increase, so you\'ll be able to exercise longer. Your body will get 50% of your calories from fat, 50% from carbohydrates and protein burn will be minimal.
Heart Rate is the number of heart beats per unit of time, typically expressed as beats per minutes (bpm).

Also called anaerobic zone. This is highly intense exercise and should be limited to no more than 10-20 minutes. Your body\'s ability to consume oxygen will increase. If you push too hard your body will start producing lactic acid. Your body will burn 85% fats and minimal percentage of protein.
Stay in this zone if your goal is to lose weight.Your body is fueled by 10% carbohydrates, 5% protein and 85% fat.
The actual number of calories burned per minute will be less than in higher zones, but you\'ll able to maintain exercise longer.
You are pushing your heart to the limits here and should consult your doctor to check if you can exercise in this zone safely.
Heart rate zones in this app are calculated from Karvonen Formula.
This zone is the least intense. You are in it just to warm up or cool down, in order to prevent injuries.

As you sleep, you go through different phases that range from deep sleep to light sleep. The phase you are in when your alarm clock goes off will impact how rested or groggy you feel when you wake. A fixed alarm clock wakes you up no matter what phase you are in your sleep. Many time, it will wake you in the middle of a deep sleep phase (sometimes while having a sweet dream) and you wake up still feeling tired.

Sleep Time always tries to wake you in your lightest sleep phase. This is the natural way to wake up where you feel rested and rejuvenated. Sleep Time uses the sensitive accelerometer built into your iPhone to monitor your movements and determine your sleep phase.
Sleep Time uses the phone\'s accelerometer to sense your movement as you sleep.
It is important that you place your phone on the mattress where it will not fall off the bed, or bother you while you sleep. We recommend the top corner of the mattress, out of the way of the pillow.
Please refer to the Azumio web site and Wikipedia for more information about sleep in general and how the Sleep Time application works.
Sleep Time will monitor your movement throughout the night to determine your sleep cycle and wake you softly, when you are in the lightest possible sleep phase.
Sleep Time creates a 30 minute wake-up phase that ends at your desired alarm time.
You can snooze the alarm by simply picking up the phone but we recommend you wake up when the alarm goes off.
Soundscapes can help you fall asleep more easily in a noisy environment, such as in a city or near a highway, or just help you relax after a stressful day.

From the soundscapes tab, choose a soundscape from our Azumio collection. When you start the alarm, you will notice a musical note icon on the upper left of the alarm screen. This icon lets you start or stop soundscapes directly from the alarm screen. You can also use the soundscapes audio button on the alarm screen in case you need to pause or resume soundscapes after you have started your alarm.

You may set the soundscapes to play for any duration that you like. When the soundscape is scheduled to turn off, Sleep Time will gradually decrease the volume so that you are not awoken by any sudden changes in ambient sound.
